data.chText: 阿司匹林（镇痛解热消炎药）
data.enText: a drug used to reduce pain, fever and inflammation
Take two aspirin(s) for a headache.

means: 阿司匹林(镇痛解热消炎药)

tr: the acetylated derivative of salicylic acid
used as an analgesic anti-inflammatory drug (trade names Bayer, Empirin, and St. Joseph) usually taken in tablet form
slows clotting of the blood by poisoning platelets

value.def: Aspirin is a mild drug which reduces pain and fever.
